         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="parallels">MaitrSiŋgim, Taf. 146-148</note><note type="philcomment">This fragment contains the end of the fourteenth and the beginning of the fifteenth act of the Maitreyasamitināṭaka; the colophon of act 14 is contained in line a8, line b1-8 already cover the beginning of act 15. An Uy. parallel is MaitrSiŋgim, Taf. 146 v.6-147 r.28 (act 14, <bibl><title corresp="ref:tekin1980"/><citedRange>115-6</citedRange></bibl>) to Taf. 148 (act 15, <bibl><title corresp="ref:tekin1980"/><citedRange>117</citedRange></bibl>), where the colophon is in Taf. 147 r.21-28 (<bibl><title corresp="ref:tekin1980"/><citedRange>116</citedRange></bibl>). See also <bibl><title corresp="ref:pinault1999"/><citedRange>201-202</citedRange></bibl>.</note><note corresp="#b3" type="philcomment">The restoration <hi>(ś)l(a) (ri)s</hi> is based on Siegling's personal copy of <bibl><title corresp="ref:siegandsiegling1921"/><ref target="https://www.univie.ac.at/tocharian/images/TS_Siegling/TS_Siegling_Page_157.png" type="external">157</ref></bibl>. The collocation <hi>ris waṣtu</hi> also occurs in <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a254"/> a3 (as pointed out by Anna Kuritsyna via Ilya Itkin, 18 November 2015).</note><note corresp="#b3 #b4" type="philcomment">The restoration <hi>(kumbhā)ṇḍāśśi</hi> (cf. <bibl><title corresp="ref:mullerandsieg1916"/><citedRange>406</citedRange></bibl>) is based on the <ref target="#b3b4" type="external">Uy. parallel of the sentence</ref>.</note><note corresp="#b3 #b4" type="philcomment"><distinct type="ms_text">/// (kumbhā)ṇḍāśśi wak klyoṣtär :</distinct> corresponds to <distinct type="ms_text">.../l'r kwymp'nty l'r nynk (')wyn l(')ry yštylwr</distinct> (<bibl><title corresp="ref:tekin1980"/><citedRange>117</citedRange></bibl>)</note></p>
